						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar set up in front of the Pātāḷa-Sōmēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Indra (III), 925 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 848, Pārthiva, Uttarāyaṇasaṁkrānti.</hi> The detailes given are insufficient for verification. However, the <hi rend="italic">saṁkrānti,</hi> occurred on <hi rend="bold">December 23,</hi> the year corresponding to <hi rend="bold">925 A.D.</hi> The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the construction of the door-way and the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa,</hi> and the repair of the shrines for the eight <hi rend="italic">parivāra-dēvatas</hi> of the Muḻkiṁṭīśvara temple, by a <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmanta</hi> whose name cannot be made out, when Pallava-dhīra was governing <hi rend="bold">Muḷki-500</hi> division. The record states that the king, <hi rend="bold">Indra III,</hi> was ruling the <hi rend="italic">mahāraṭṭarājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
